section.para:
 At level 1, the following additional distinctions may be made in an encoding: 


the label element may be used for heading-like titles
      appearing in the middle of a division;



the quote element may be used to distinguish passages such
      as quotations, epigraphs, stretches of verse, letters etc. embedded in the running text;




the corr element may be used to indicate a passage
      (typically a word or phrase) which is clearly erroneous or nonstandard in the original and
      which has been editorially corrected; 



the elements foreign, emph, or
       title are available and should be used in preference to hi for passages rendered in a different font or otherwise made
      visually salient in the source, where an encoder can do so with confidence; 



the element gap may be used to indicate where some component
      of a source (typically an illustration) has been left out; 



the elements note and ref may
      be used to capture the location and content of authorially supplied footnotes or end-notes;
      wherever they occur in the source, notes must be collected together in a div
       type="notes" within a back element.
